For this task, we could observe real life banks. Nowadays, banks are widely used to do money
and transactional operations. From what we know, variability could be the amount of customers.
A chain of people lending and borrowing money from banks could explain the interconnectedness.
For example, if a person fail to pay off their debts, it would also cause financial loss to the
bank. This not only affects the bank, but other customers too. Complexity comes from many
processes and stakeholders involved. A bank must manage deposits, loans, transfers and etc. All
of these processes interact with each other. A change in one area, can affect multiple departments
and processes throughout the bank. We could also find another example in customer service.
Different customers require different amount of time, so some transactions could be quick,
like a few minutes, or long depending on their needs. This may affect other customers by
decreasing or increasing the wait time.
